  <front>
   <head>SONNET. TO DELIA.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">THRICE has the year its varied circuit run,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And chearful, Delia, have the moments flown,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Since with my love for thee, my care begun</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To form thy tender mind to virtue prone:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The flatteries of my sex I bade thee shun,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I bade thee shun the follies of thy own;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Fictitious manners by example won,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Alike to truth and innocence unknown:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Say, blooming Maiden, in whose gentle breast</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Reigns simple Nature undisguis'd by Art,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Now amply try'd by time's unerring test,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">How just the dictates of this faithful heart,</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">That with the joys thy favouring smiles impart,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Deems all its cares repair'd, itself supremely blest.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
